import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud

# Load the data
file_path = 'youtube.csv'
data = pd.read_csv(file_path)

# Check for missing values
missing_values = data.isnull().sum()

# Remove duplicates
data_cleaned = data.drop_duplicates()

# Distribution of Categories
category_distribution = data_cleaned['category'].value_counts()

# Title Length Analysis
data_cleaned['title_length'] = data_cleaned['title'].apply(len)

# Description Length Analysis
data_cleaned['description_length'] = data_cleaned['description'].apply(len)

# Common Keywords in Titles
all_titles = ' '.join(data_cleaned['title'].tolist())
wordcloud_titles = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white').generate(all_titles)

# Common Keywords in Descriptions
all_descriptions = ' '.join(data_cleaned['description'].tolist())
wordcloud_descriptions = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white').generate(all_descriptions)

# Plotting
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 12))

# Category Distribution
axes[0, 0].bar(category_distribution.index, category_distribution.values, color='skyblue')
axes[0, 0].set_title('Distribution of Categories')
axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Category')
axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Number of Videos')

# Title Length Distribution
axes[0, 1].hist(data_cleaned['title_length'], bins=20, color='lightgreen')
axes[0, 1].set_title('Title Length Distribution')
axes[0, 1].set_xlabel('Length of Title')
axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Frequency')

# Word Cloud for Titles
axes[1, 0].imshow(wordcloud_titles, interpolation='bilinear')
axes[1, 0].axis('off')
axes[1, 0].set_title('Common Keywords in Titles')

# Word Cloud for Descriptions
axes[1, 1].imshow(wordcloud_descriptions, interpolation='bilinear')
axes[1, 1].axis('off')
axes[1, 1].set_title('Common Keywords in Descriptions')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
